observations.recommendation:
We recommended that Management instruct the:

Municipal GSO to prepare an IIRUP for the unserviceable PPE and conduct inspection/appraisal by the Appraisal and Inspection Team with the presence of the Auditor and submit the same to the Municipal Accountant. If found to be valuable, the same shall be sold for public auction in accordance with Section 79 of PD No. 1445; 
Municipal GSO to exert all effort to coordinate with concerned accountable officers to find the missing/ lost PPEs, otherwise, request for relief from accountability to the audit team;

Municipal Accountant to cease the recording of Depreciation Expense for the demolished properties; and


d.	Municipal GSO and Municipal Accountant to reconcile the RPCPPE and accounting records and to derecognize the sidecars already donated to the intended recipients.

We recommended that Management:

conduct all succeeding procurements in pursuance to Section 3 of the Revised IRR of RA No. 9184;

pay directly to the supplier for any of the LGU’s obligations pursuant to COA Circular No. 97-002 dated February 10, 1997

We recommended that Management instruct the:
Municipal GSO to prepare an IIRUP for the unserviceable PPE and conduct inspection/appraisal by the Appraisal and Inspection Team with the presence of the Auditor and submit the same to the Municipal Accountant. If found to be valuable, the same shall be sold for public auction in accordance with Section 79 of PD No. 1445;
Municipal GSO to exert all effort to coordinate with concerned accountable officers to find the missing/lost PPEs, otherwise, request for relief from accountability to the audit team;
Municipal Accountant to cease the recording of Depreciation Expense for the demolished properties; and
Municipal GSO and Municipal Accountant to reconcile the RPCPPE and accounting records and to derecognize the sidecars already donated to the intended recipients.

We recommended that:
The LCE/Mun. Engineer explain in writing the circumstances surrounding  the demolition of the building;
Management submit the Inventory and Inspection Report, photographs, as well as the Waste Material Report;
Management to strictly follow the guidelines on the divestment or disposal of property and other assets as provided under COA Circular No. 89-296 dated January 27, 1989.
